    \begin {tikzcd}
    m\ar [r, "a", shift left=.2em]\ar [r, "b"', shift right=.2em] &
    w\ar [r, "f"]\ar [d, "e"', two heads] & x\ar [d, "m",
    hookrightarrow] \\
    & y\ar [r, "g"'] & z\makebox [0pt][l]{.}
    \end {tikzcd}


 Since e coequalizes a and b, mfa = gea = geb = mfb, so since
  m is a monomorphism, fa = fb. Now f coequalizes a and
  b, so there is a lift y\to  x which factors f through e. Since e
  is an epi, further this lift factors g through m.

Let x\xrightarrow {f} y be any map. Then because the quotient of f
  exists, we have a diagram 




